NetworkSet: # Use this sheet to define settings for Ethernet networks to be created in OneView.
# If the row starts with '#' it will be ignored by the script
# For specific settings - See Definition below

# List of networkset names 
# where a given network can belong to
# Use '|' as separator
# Note: a network can belong to multipe network sets
NSTypicalBandwidth:
# List of associated typical bandwidth 
# defined for a given network set
# Use '| as separator
# Value range: [2, 20000]
NSMaximumBandwidth:
# List of associated MAX bandwidth 
# defined for a given network set
# Use '| as separator
# Value range: [100, 20000]
UplinkSet:
# Note: if the networkset is already used in server profile, 
# when you add new network, 
# you need to provide the
#uplinkset and 
#associated Logical Interconnect Group
LogicalInterConnectGroup:
# Note: if the networkset is already used in server profile, 
# when you add new network, 
# you need to provide the
#uplinkset and 
#associated Logical Interconnect Group
Subnet:
# N/A for C7000
# Subnet name as defined in Addresses and Identifiers
